commands.detail:
pushd [ -qsLP ] [ arg ]

pushd [ -qsLP ] old new

pushd [ -qsLP ] {+|-}n Change the current directory, and push the old
current directory onto the directory stack. In the first form, change
the current directory to arg. If arg is not specified, change to the
second directory on the stack (that is, exchange the top two entries),
or change to $HOME if the PUSHD_TO_HOME option is set or if there is
only one entry on the stack. Otherwise, arg is interpreted as it would
be by cd. The meaning of old and new in the second form is also the same
as for cd.
